metamanager (2.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Separated plugin from daemon package.
  * This package now ships only the OS-level daemons (compress + metadata),
    systemd units, and the installer script.
  * The WordPress plugin is now in a separate repository:
    github.com/richardkentgates/metamanager-plugin
  * Installer fetches plugin from the new repository.
  * Updated debian/control description to reflect daemon-only scope.
  * Updated debian/metamanager.install to exclude plugin files.

 -- Richard Kent Gates <mail@richardkentgates.com>  Wed, 22 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0500

metamanager (2.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package.
  * Thin package: stages plugin tree, daemons, and systemd units to
    /usr/local/lib/metamanager; postinst runs metamanager-install.sh --no-deps
    to auto-detect WordPress, copy the plugin, patch daemons, enable services,
    and activate the plugin via WP-CLI.
  * Depends declare jq, inotify-tools, exiftool, jpegtran, optipng, webp,
    ffmpeg so apt provisions them; the --no-deps flag keeps the postinst from
    re-running apt-get.
  * Syncs version strings (header 2.1.7 / constant 2.2.0 -> 2.3.0) and adds
    the --no-deps flag to metamanager-install.sh.

 -- Richard Kent Gates <mail@richardkentgates.com>  Tue, 07 Jul 2026 11:13:06 -0500
